        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 15 at 7:24PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 724 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Oppelo, or near Perryville, moving southwest at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Morrilton...                      Perryville...
Oppelo...                         Perry...
Adona...                          Houston...
Petit Jean State Park...          Sequoya Park...
Casa...                           Aplin...
Birta...                          Antioch in Perry County...
Ada...                            Nimrod...
Deberrie...                       Pontoon...
Oak Grove in Perry County...      Long Mountain...
Thornburg...                      Cherry Hill in Perry County...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
